\begin{align*}
ab+c&=4k+a+b+c\
\Rightarrow\qquad ab+c\equiv a+b+c\pmod{2}.
\end{align*}

Since $a$ is odd, $a+b+c$ is odd if and only if $b+c$ is odd. Since $b$ and $c$ are chosen randomly from $\{1,2,3,4,5\}$, the probability that $b+c$ is odd is $\frac{1}{5}$.

